Dorian isn’t borion. Here’s why.
✌️ First, stop thinking of modes as the major scale starting from different notes. Start thinking of a mode as a world of sound to explore and live in. So let’s rewind back to 1959 to Miles Davis ‘Kind of Blue’. The era of musicians wearing suits and modal jazz. But modes aren’t just for jazz, in fact they are still used today — you’re likely already playing a mode, right now. A la mode. tu meke 🫶

If you really want to learn to solo, there’s no better place than the Soloing Learning Pathway which we just dropped on @pickupmusic, taught by myself, @karl_kerfoot, with guest artists @guitarianna and @rafasgreatesthits. It’s 6 grades of lessons, I’ll walk you through 7 modes in 7 days in grade 3
